  <h1>Post-Storm Inspection in Madeira</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    Inspection after storms, heavy rain and intense weather periods – for owners who want a clear and reliable understanding of their property's condition after severe weather.
  </p>

  <p>
    Madeira offers exceptional locations, open terraces, ocean views and high-end properties in often exposed settings. These qualities make a property highly attractive, but they also increase its exposure to wind, rain, water accumulation and visible changes after weather events.
  </p>

</section>

<section class="text-flow">

  <h2>Why a post-storm inspection is valuable</h2>

  <p>
    Many high-end properties in Madeira are not occupied year-round. During periods of absence, it often remains unclear after severe weather whether everything is still in order or whether visible issues have already developed.
  </p>

  <h3>Typical risks after weather events</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>shifted or loosened exterior elements</li>
    <li>visible strain on windows, doors and transition points</li>
    <li>water accumulation and blocked drainage areas</li>
    <li>toppled plants or affected garden areas</li>
    <li>disorder and visible signs of strong wind pressure</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    A structured inspection provides exactly what is missing from a distance: clarity, assessment and a reliable basis for the next decisions.
  </p>

</section>

