<section class="text-flow">

  <h2>Water, moisture and sensitive transition points</h2>

  <p>
    In Madeira, intense rainfall can bring considerable amounts of water in a short time. Not every consequence is immediately dramatic, which is exactly why this area is especially important.
  </p>

  <h3>Main points of attention</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>visible water accumulation</li>
    <li>moisture around doors, windows and transition areas</li>
    <li>signs of water ingress</li>
    <li>areas that require further observation</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Early recognition of moisture is one of the decisive factors in preventing later damage to high-end properties.
  </p>

</section>

<section class="text-flow">

  <h2>Clear feedback instead of uncertainty</h2>

  <p>
    After the inspection, you do not receive a vague note, but a calm and understandable assessment of the situation.
  </p>

  <h3>You receive</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>a clear summary of the inspection</li>
    <li>photo documentation of relevant areas</li>
    <li>a clear explanation of visible irregularities</li>
    <li>guidance on whether observation is sufficient or further action is advisable</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    This clarity is essential for owners who need to make sound decisions from a distance without relying on speculation.
  </p>

</section>

